FBIS3-53417 "drnes010_s_94001" FBIS-NES-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 Iran Two Bombs Explode in Central Tehran; 3 Injured LD1301202394 Tehran IRNA in English 2010 GMT 13 Jan 94 LD1301202394 Tehran IRNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tehran, Jan. 13, IRNA -- Following the blast at Ferdowsi Square at 20:30 hours here Thursday, reports said two bombs had been placed in a corner street garbage bin. Police is investigating into the incident. A police officer said he could not comment until the end of investigations. He observed that the bombs were very small and were of the sound type. The windowpanes of a sandwitch shop and a nearby bookshop were shattered as a result of the blast. The IRNA reporter saw an ambulance taking three injured persons to a nearby hospital. All the three were innocent passers-by. The emergency hospital of Tehran said one of the victims is criticially injured. The area is one of the busiest in central Tehran but fortunately shops were closed at the time of the blast and pedestrians were few.
